Text-TypingEffort version 0.23
========================

DESCRIPTION

Text::TypingEffort is used to calculate how much physical effort was
required to type a given text. Several metrics of effort are used.  For
further information, consult the POD.

A small script ("effort") is included so that you can quickly examine
the amount of effort it would take to type a given file or files.
Run "effort --help" for usage.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Build.PL
   ./Build
   ./Build test
   ./Build install

DEPENDENCIES

   Test::More - version 0.31 or higher
   Getopt::Std - if you want to use the effort script

